article.headline: Illinois State 80, Drake 65
article.story: NORMAL, Ill. (AP) -- Levi Dyer scored 27 points Sunday to lead Illinois State to a 80-65 victory over Drake. The Redbirds (11-9, 3-6 Missouri Valley) shot well from the field from the start of the game, building a 34-24 halftime lead. Illinois State held the lead for the rest of the game, despite Drake's 14 points off Redbird turnovers. Dyer sunk a career-high five 3-pointers, and Illinois State as a team hit 51 percent of its shots. Ajay Calvin led Drake (11-9, 2-7) with 15 points and grabbed 10 rebounds. Jonathan Cox came off the bench to add 14 points and five rebounds before fouling out with 50.3 seconds left. For the Redbirds, Boo Richardson scored 16 points and Anthony Slack added 14.
